Data availability

            The ERA5 reanalysis data are from https://www.ecmwf.int/en/forecasts/datasets/reanalysis-datasets/era5. The MSWEP precipitation data are from https://www.gloh2o.org/mswep/. The JRA-3Q reanalysis data are from https://gdex.ucar.edu/datasets/d640000/dataaccess/#. The CRU precipitation data are from https://crudata.uea.ac.uk/cru/data/hrg/index.htm#current. The GPCC precipitation data are from https://www.dwd.de/EN/ourservices/gpcc/gpcc.html. The NCEP–NCAR reanalysis sea-level pressure data are from https://psl.noaa.gov/data/gridded/data.ncep.reanalysis.html. The NAO index data are from https://crudata.uea.ac.uk/cru/data/nao/nao.dat. The MERRA-2 dataset is from https://doi.org/10.5067/RKPHT8KC1Y1T. The CESM2-LE data are from https://www.cesm.ucar.edu/community-projects/lens2/data-sets. The CMIP6 data are from https://esgf-node.ipsl.upmc.fr/search/cmip6-ipsl/. The nudged CESM2 simulations used for the analysis are available from https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19150219 (ref. 67).
          Code availability

            The R (version 4.2.2) code used for data analysis is available at the repository in an Open Science Framework repository (https://osf.io/7xjma/?view_only=cff2af1a670b48749f09160f0b3492c4). All of the figures are generated using R (version 4.2.2). All base maps are produced using open-source coastline data (coastsCoarse) from the R package ‘fields’.
